Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} off stems and finely chop 1 tsp. Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}(finely chopped). In a #medium bowl{}, soak @white bread{1%slice} with @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water.

Break bread up with your hands until pasty. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, sun-dried tomatoes, shallot, half the garlic, half the rosemary, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix with your hands until just combined. Form into two oval loaves and place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake until cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and dice @russet potato{12%ounce}(peeled and diced) into 1/2-inch cubes. Place potatoes and a large pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #medium pot{}. Add enough water to cover, then bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook until potatoes are tender, about ~{12%minutes}.

With 15 minutes left to go on meatloaf, toss @green beans{6%ounce} in a medium bowl with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Spread on baking sheet with meatloaf and roast until green beans are tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

Drain potatoes once tender. In same #pot{}, heat @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining garlic, and remaining rosemary over medium heat. Cook until melted and fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add potatoes and @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until very smooth. Add a splash of water (or milk) to loosen, if necessary. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Plate mashed potatoes, then top with roasted green beans and meatloaf.

> You could think of this recipe as what happens when an American classic spends a semester abroad in Italy. Featuring adorable, quick-cooking mini-meatloaves spiked with sun-dried tomatoes and garlic, it's a familiar dish with Mediterranean flair. These loaves haven't forgotten their roots though: we're sticking with tradition and serving these loaves with the requisite green beans and mashed potatoes.